children.subject: I'm taking bioe105 for the circuits part of 16A but that's this next fall, so I won't have covered it since I'd have to start it the same semester as 16b. Do you think I can just take 16b this next semester and take 47D or 16A later, after 16B?
This is only true if you're an L&S CS major; it's not true for EECS.

I think you can enroll in EECS 16B with Math 54 (unless that's changed in the Fall 2020)

You only need to fill in your circuits knowledge from EECS 16A
Just learn module 2 from 16B and you will be fine.

history.content: You can check in with your ESS advisor, but the requirement for EECS is 16B. You already are using the argument that BioE 105 and Math 54 have the same material as 16A in order to replace 16A (and I should note that if the College approves your petition which would include 1 unit of 47D, BioE 105 would count as an overlap for your double major). You can't use the same argument again to replace a second required course.

Hi!

I had a question about 16B. I'm currently a sophomore who hasn't taken 16A yet(I'm a double in bioe and took Math 54). I've seen a lot of the emails trying to force students into taking 16B and I can't yet because I lack the prerequisite for it, and the department seems fairly insistent on not letting upperclassmen take the class the in the future.

I've been planning to take bioe 105 this next fall, and Heather told me that I would be able to take 47D, probably in the spring, for one unit after 105. I had hoped to take 47E as well afterwards considering the overlap in content with 54 and bioe105 (especially because I've already taken other UD courses, eg 189), but I'm wondering how enrollment would work for that. I realize that by then there will be no more priority for upperclassmen in 16B (but this is already the case for me since I can't take it this fall without 16A). 

Is there any way to guarantee that I can enroll in EECS47E after 54 and bioe105? I worry that, since I cannot enroll in 16B this semester, I will not be able to satisfy that requirement (and would have to drop my double major)

Thanks!
